### 8. Separate Threading Models

```java
// GOOD: Single-threaded consumer, multi-threaded processing
ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(10);

try (KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props)) {
    consumer.subscribe(topics);

    while (running) {
        ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));

        for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
            // Submit to thread pool (don't call consumer methods from executor threads)
            executor.submit(() -> processRecord(record));
        }
    }
}

executor.shutdown();
executor.awaitTermination(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
```

**Key constraint:** Only call consumer methods from consumer thread. Use queues to communicate with processing threads.

