## Rebalancing and Callbacks

### ConsumerRebalanceListener

Implement to handle partition assignment changes.

```java
public class MyRebalanceListener implements ConsumerRebalanceListener {
    private KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer;
    private DatabaseConnection db;

    public MyRebalanceListener(KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer,
                               DatabaseConnection db) {
        this.consumer = consumer;
        this.db = db;
    }

    @Override
    public void onPartitionsRevoked(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
        // Called when about to lose partitions
        // Safe to commit offsets here
        System.out.println("Revoked: " + partitions);

        try {
            consumer.commitSync();  // Commit pending offsets
        } catch (CommitFailedException e) {
            log.error("Commit failed during revocation", e);
        }

        // Save any state/close resources
        for (TopicPartition tp : partitions) {
            db.savePartitionState(tp);
        }
    }

    @Override
    public void onPartitionsAssigned(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
        // Called when partitions assigned after rebalance
        // Safe to initialize positions here
        System.out.println("Assigned: " + partitions);

        // Restore saved state
        for (TopicPartition tp : partitions) {
            long savedOffset = db.getSavedOffset(tp);
            if (savedOffset >= 0) {
                consumer.seek(tp, savedOffset);
            } else {
                consumer.seekToBeginning(Arrays.asList(tp));
            }
        }
    }

    @Override
    public void onPartitionsLost(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
        // Called when partitions lost without revocation
        // (e.g., session timeout)
        System.out.println("Lost: " + partitions);
        // Do NOT commit offsets - they're already owned by other consumers
        // Clean up resources only
    }
}

// Register listener
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("orders"), new MyRebalanceListener(consumer, db));
```

### Callback Execution Details

**Execution context:**
- Callbacks execute on consumer thread during `poll()` call
- NO special threading; they block the polling thread
- Exceptions propagate to `poll()` caller
- Safe to call consumer methods inside callbacks (e.g., `commitSync()`, `seek()`)

**Callback order (normal rebalance):**
1. `onPartitionsRevoked()` - revoke old partitions
2. [Network rebalance coordination]
3. `onPartitionsAssigned()` - assign new partitions

**Callback order (timeout/loss scenario):**
1. `onPartitionsLost()` - lose partitions unexpectedly
2. May not have `onPartitionsRevoked()` call

**Protocol differences:**

| Aspect | Classic (Eager) | Cooperative |
|--------|-----------------|-------------|
| All partitions revoked | Always (even if none assigned) | Only those being revoked |
| `onPartitionsAssigned` receives | All newly assigned partitions | Only truly new partitions |
| Rebalance duration | Longer (all stop) | Shorter (incremental) |
| Suitable for | Simple cases | High-throughput (faster stabilization) |

### Exception Handling in Callbacks

```java
public class SafeRebalanceListener implements ConsumerRebalanceListener {
    @Override
    public void onPartitionsRevoked(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
        try {
            consumer.commitSync();
        } catch (CommitFailedException e) {
            // Not retriable from here - just log
            log.error("Commit failed during revocation", e);
            // Continue anyway - revocation still happens
        } catch (WakeupException e) {
            // Can re-throw WakeupException if needed
            throw e;
        }
    }

    @Override
    public void onPartitionsAssigned(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
        // Exceptions here propagate to poll() caller
        try {
            restoreOffsetsFromDatabase(partitions);
        } catch (DatabaseException e) {
            // Wrap as KafkaException for consistency
            throw new KafkaException("Failed to restore offsets", e);
        }
    }
}
```

**Important semantics:**
- Throwing exception from callback does NOT prevent assignment change
- Assignment is updated internally regardless of callback exception
- Exception propagates to `poll()` caller
- Re-throwing `WakeupException` or `InterruptException` is allowed

