## Subscription and Assignment

### Dynamic Subscription (Group-Managed)

Consumer group coordinator automatically manages partition assignment.

```java
// Subscribe to specific topics
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic1", "topic2"), listener);

// Subscribe with rebalance listener (recommended)
consumer.subscribe(
    Arrays.asList("orders", "returns"),
    new ConsumerRebalanceListener() {
        @Override
        public void onPartitionsRevoked(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
            // Save offsets for graceful shutdown
            consumer.commitSync();
        }

        @Override
        public void onPartitionsAssigned(Collection<TopicPartition> partitions) {
            // Initialize any state needed for new partitions
        }
    }
);

// Get current subscription
Set<String> topics = consumer.subscription();
```

**Semantics:**
- Topics can be added/removed dynamically between polls
- Subscription change triggers rebalance on next `poll()`
- Regex subscription updates topic list on each `poll()` based on broker metadata
- Only one subscription mode per consumer (subscribe OR assign)

### Manual Assignment (Standalone)

Consumer directly controls partition assignment without group coordination.

```java
// Manually assign partitions
consumer.assign(Arrays.asList(
    new TopicPartition("orders", 0),
    new TopicPartition("orders", 1),
    new TopicPartition("orders", 2)
));

// Get current assignment
Set<TopicPartition> partitions = consumer.assignment();

// Unsubscribe/unassign (resets to empty)
consumer.unsubscribe();
```

**Behavioral differences from subscription:**
- No rebalancing occurs
- No group coordination
- Partitions never reassigned unless manually changed
- Consumer doesn't heartbeat to broker
- No `max.poll.interval.ms` enforcement
- Useful for standalone consumers or precise partition control

### Subscription vs. Assignment

**Use subscription when:**
- Building fault-tolerant consumer groups
- Multiple consumers share work
- Automatic load balancing desired
- Partition count changes dynamically

**Use assignment when:**
- Building standalone consumers
- Precise partition control needed
- Testing/debugging specific partitions
- Building custom rebalancing logic

